import scala.collection.immutable.Map

def drawHistogram(sample: Array[Double], M: Int): Unit = {
    val (a, b) = (sample.min, sample.max)
    val interval = (b - a) / M
    val grouped = groupToBins(sample, M, a, b, interval).toSeq.sortBy(_._1)
    println("%table\nx\tp")
    grouped.foreach(kv => println(a + kv._1 * interval + "\t" + kv._2))
}

def drawHistogramDiscret(sample: Array[Double], M: Int): Unit = {
    val (a, b) = (sample.min, sample.max)
    val interval = (b - a) / M
    val grouped = groupToBinsDiscret(sample, M, a, b, interval).toSeq.sortBy(_._1)
    println("%table\nx\tp")
    grouped.foreach(kv => println(a + kv._1 * interval + "\t" + kv._2))
}

### Lets set the distribution using probability matrix:

msg.data: Lets set the distribution using probability matrix:

paragraphs.text:
def generateDiscretDistibution(
    discretDistribution: Array[Array[Int]], 
    xMin: Double,
    xMax: Double,
    yMin: Double,
    yMax: Double,
    r: LinearCongruentGenerator,
    size: Int): Array[(Double, Double)] =  {
        
    val cumSum = createCumSum(discretDistribution.map(_.sum))
    val(n, m) = (discretDistribution.length, discretDistribution(0).length)
    val xInterval = (xMax - xMin) / n
    val yInterval = (yMax - yMin) / m
    
    @tailrec
    def iter(arr: ArrayBuffer[(Double, Double)], cumSum: Array[Double], i: Int): Array[(Double, Double)] = {
        if(i == 0) return arr.toArray
        
        val rv = r.next
        val xIndex = cumSum.count(_ < rv)
        val xValue = xMin + xIndex * xInterval + 0.5 * xInterval
        val xRow = discretDistribution(xIndex)
        
        val cumSum2 = createCumSum(xRow)
        val rv2 = r.next
        val yIndex = cumSum2.count(_ < rv2)   
        val yValue = yMin + yIndex * yInterval + 0.5 * yInterval
        
        iter(arr += Tuple2(xValue, yValue), cumSum, i - 1)
    }
    
    iter(ArrayBuffer.empty[(Double, Double)], cumSum, size)
}

val(n, m) = (discretDistribution.length, discretDistribution(0).length)
val xInterval = (xMax - xMin) / n
val yInterval = (yMax - yMin) / m
val Y_INDEXES = 0 until m

var s = new Array[Double](0)
var dconditionalStatisticsX = ArrayBuffer.empty[ConditionalStatistics]
Y_INDEXES.foreach(yi => {
    val yValue = yMin + (yi + 0.5) * yInterval
    val s = xByY(dsample10e5, nearw(yValue))
    val yVect = discretDistribution.map(row => row(yi))
    val xValues = ((xMin + 0.5 * xInterval) to (xMax - 0.5 * xInterval) by xInterval).toArray
    
    val dchi2 = dcalcXi2(s, mapToProbabilities(yVect), xValues, 0, 0.05)
    
    dconditionalStatisticsX += ConditionalStatistics(s"y = ${yValue}", s.length, mean(s), calcIntervalStatistic(s, 10, mean), variance(s), calcIntervalStatistic(s, 10, variance), dchi2)
})

println("%table\ncondition\tlength\tmean\tintervalMean\tvariance\tintervalVariance\tchi2")
dconditionalStatisticsX.foreach(stats => println(stats.condition + "\t" + stats.length + "\t" + stats.mean + "\t" + stats.intervalMean + "\t" + stats.variance + "\t" + stats.intervalVariance + "\t" + stats.chi2))
